---
title: Dapp ↔ Iframe ↔ Popup — Core Flows
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Dapp SDK<br/>(any origin)
    participant I as Hidden Iframe<br/>(wallet.aztec.network/pxe)
    participant P as Popup<br/>(wallet.aztec.network/auth)
    participant A as Authenticator<br/>(Secure Element)

    Note over D,I: Secure channel established (see secure-channel-diagram)

    Note over D,A: CONNECT — register passkey + compute address

    D->>I: encrypt(keyA, { method: "connect" })
    I->>P: window.open("wallet.aztec.network/auth")

    alt First visit
        P->>A: credentials.create() + PRF
        A-->>P: publicKey(x,y) + credentialId + PRF(32B)
        P->>P: HKDF(PRF) → accountSalt
        P->>I: postMessage({ publicKey, credentialId, accountSalt })
        I->>I: Compute address, store credentialId + publicKey in IndexedDB
    else Returning visit
        I->>I: Load credentialId + publicKey from IndexedDB
        I->>I: Compute address from stored publicKey
    end

    I-->>D: encrypt(keyB, { result: { address } })

    Note over D,A: PRIVATE READ — biometric every time (keys never stored)

    D->>I: encrypt(keyA, { method: "executeUtility", params: { ... } })
    I->>P: postMessage({ type: "derive-keys" })
    P->>A: credentials.get({ allowCredentials: [credentialId] }) + PRF
    A-->>P: PRF(32B) — biometric required
    P->>P: HKDF(PRF) → protocol keys
    P->>I: postMessage({ type: "session-keys", protocolKeys })
    I->>I: PXE executes with keys → discard keys immediately
    I-->>D: encrypt(keyB, { result: { decoded } })

    Note over D,A: SEND TX — PRF for keys + WebAuthn for signing

    D->>I: encrypt(keyA, { method: "sendTx", params: { calls } })
    I->>P: postMessage({ type: "sign-tx", outer_hash, txDetails })
    P->>P: Show tx approval UI
    P->>A: credentials.get({ challenge: outer_hash }) + PRF
    A-->>P: signature + authData + clientDataJSON + PRF(32B)
    P->>P: HKDF(PRF) → protocol keys
    P->>I: postMessage({ type: "auth-witness", authWitness, protocolKeys })
    I->>I: ZK proof → submit → discard keys immediately
    I-->>D: encrypt(keyB, { result: { txHash } })

    rect rgb(45, 45, 60)
        Note over D,I: SECURITY BOUNDARY
        Note right of D: Dapp never receives: keys, PRF, notes
        Note right of P: Popup ↔ iframe is same-origin (no encryption needed)
        Note right of I: Keys exist only for the duration of a single operation
    end
